 "draftNote": "2 of five queued off a bottom-two lane: Cuban Noobster (midlane\u2192carry), Willy Guggenheim (offlane\u2192jungle).",
 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A 3-stack run off the map \u2014 towers 1\u20139, objectives 4\u201325. The two solo lanes held even but the team got sieged out by 27 minutes.",
  "team": "Trio of you (Willy/Cuban/Xeebs) plus two randoms; the map collapsed (1 tower to 9). Xeebs' Crunch fed 9 deaths (his Khaimera norm is 5) and the jungle losing that hard hands over every objective. The lane matchups were close-to-fine on pred.gg \u2014 this was a fights-and-map loss, not a draft one.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Stop forcing fights when behind on towers \u2014 Xeebs especially. Play for vision and a single Fangtooth pick instead of feeding the siege.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Crunch jungle, 1/9 \u2014 9 deaths vs your 5 norm. The jungler feeding doubles the map loss; when towers are slipping, path safe and stop diving.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "The Fey mid (2/5) into a slightly favored Wraith (57%) \u2014 you had the edge on paper and went even; the loss was the map, not your lane.",
